=================================================================
F. QUANTITATIVE BIAS ANALYSIS
=================================================================
  Assumptions:
    U = complex surgery (long CPB / cross-clamp)
    OR_UY = effect of complex surgery on AKI
    p0 = P(complex | untreated), p1 = p0 - delta
    Bias factor = (OR_UY*p1 + 1-p1) / (OR_UY*p0 + 1-p0)
    Adjusted OR = Observed OR / Bias factor

  ── AC primary (eICU) (observed OR = 0.755) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.824 → adjusted OR=0.917 (still protective)
  ── IPTW (eICU) (observed OR = 0.774) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.824 → adjusted OR=0.940 (still protective)
  ── Mg >2.3 OW (eICU) (observed OR = 0.629) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.690 (still protective)
  ── Mg >2.3 AC (eICU) (observed OR = 0.535) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.587 (still protective)
  ── 2.6-3.0 subband (observed OR = 0.350) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.384 (still protective)

-----------------------------------------------------------------
QBA SUMMARY: Does the estimate survive?
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  Scenario: OR_UY=2.0, p0=0.40, delta=0.10 (moderate assumptions)
  For stratified estimates, delta halved to 0.05

  AC primary (eICU)         OR 0.755 → 0.813 ✓ survives
  IPTW (eICU)               OR 0.774 → 0.834 ✓ survives
  Mg >2.3 OW (eICU)         OR 0.629 → 0.652 ✓ survives
  Mg >2.3 AC (eICU)         OR 0.535 → 0.555 ✓ survives
  2.6-3.0 subband           OR 0.350 → 0.363 ✓ survives

  Key insight: within the >2.3 stratum, complexity is held
  approximately constant by stratification, so the prevalence
  difference shrinks → bias factor approaches 1 → adjusted
  estimate stays protective.

